      <item>
        <title>install and use postgresql on linux</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;first we install postgresql:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-console&quot; data-lang=&quot;console&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;sudo apt-get update&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;sudo apt-get install postgresql postgresql-contrib&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then, lets set password for postgres user:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-console&quot; data-lang=&quot;console&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;sudo su postgres&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;psql&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;\password postgres&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;after typing password exit the console. 
\q&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;now lets create a database. you can do it in PSQL console, but i prefer createdb utility:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-console&quot; data-lang=&quot;console&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;createdb -h localhost -p 5432 -U postgres yourdatabasename&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where -h is host, -p is port and -U is user.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
